{"word":"παρηγορέω","slug":"παρηγορέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παρηγορέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> <el>παρηγόρουν</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ήσω</el>) (aor1 <el>-ησα</el>) (<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, aor1 <el>-ήθην</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:παρήγορος'><el>παρήγορος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to address, exhort</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to advise</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to console, appease</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}